1
00:00:01,034 --> 00:00:03,867
Desperate Housewives S01E03 Pretty Little Picture (VO+STFR&EN)

2
00:00:05,438 --> 00:00:08,271
She was his wife.
He deserves to have all the facts.

3
00:00:08,341 --> 00:00:12,209
She abandoned her husband
and her son and I'll never forgive her.

4
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:14,670
It's the age-old question.

5
00:00:14,748 --> 00:00:17,911
How much do we want to know
about our neighbors?

6
00:00:17,984 --> 00:00:20,680
Cancel the meeting
with the divorce lawyer.

7
00:00:20,754 --> 00:00:22,881
We'll find a marriage counselor.

8
00:00:22,956 --> 00:00:26,050
- I'm Mike Delfino.
- Susan Mayer. I live across the street.

9
00:00:26,126 --> 00:00:29,823
- You're gonna have to ask him out.
- I keep hoping he'll ask me out.

10
00:00:29,896 --> 00:00:31,830
I really hate the way you talk to me.

11
00:00:31,898 --> 00:00:35,061
I hate that I spent $15,000
on your diamond necklace,

12
00:00:35,135 --> 00:00:36,864
but I'm learning to deal with it.

13
00:00:36,936 --> 00:00:39,200
- Do you love him?
- I do.

14
00:00:39,272 --> 00:00:42,173
So then why are we here?
Why are we doing this?

15
00:00:42,242 --> 00:00:44,267
I don't want to wake up
one morning,

16
00:00:44,344 --> 00:00:47,438
with a sudden urge
to blow my brains out.

17
00:00:51,651 --> 00:00:53,084
After I died,

18
00:00:53,153 --> 00:00:57,886
I began to surrender the parts of myself
that were no longer necessary.

19
00:00:57,957 --> 00:01:01,791
My desires, beliefs, ambitions, doubts.

20
00:01:01,861 --> 00:01:05,957
Every trace of my humanity
was discarded.

21
00:01:06,699 --> 00:01:09,259
I discovered,
when moving through eternity,

22
00:01:09,335 --> 00:01:11,599
it helps to travel lightly.

23
00:01:12,572 --> 00:01:16,406
In fact, I held on to only one thing.

24
00:01:16,476 --> 00:01:18,103
My memory.

25
00:01:19,479 --> 00:01:23,347
It's astonishing to look back
on the world I left behind.

26
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:27,614
I remember it all. Every single detail.

27
00:01:30,290 --> 00:01:33,191
Like my friend, Bre Van De Kamp.

28
00:01:35,128 --> 00:01:38,427
I remember the easy confidence
of her smile.

29
00:01:39,632 --> 00:01:42,726
The gentle elegance of her hands.

30
00:01:43,069 --> 00:01:45,537
The refined warmth of her voice.

31
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:47,436
Bye.

32
00:01:50,009 --> 00:01:54,412
- But what I remember most about Bre...
- Rex, wasn't that a lovely...

33
00:01:54,481 --> 00:01:57,814
...was the look of fear in her eyes.

34
00:01:58,685 --> 00:02:02,052
Bre had started to realize
her world was unraveling.

35
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:05,091
And for a woman
who despised loose ends,

36
00:02:05,158 --> 00:02:08,127
that was unacceptable.

37
00:02:08,561 --> 00:02:13,555
- Rex, Rex, you need to get up.
- It's not even light out.

38
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:17,433
If the kids see you sleeping down here,
they'll start asking questions.

39
00:02:17,504 --> 00:02:22,134
- Let 'em ask. I don't care anymore.
- Well, I care.

40
00:02:22,208 --> 00:02:25,473
They don't need to be burdened
with our marital problems.

41
00:02:25,545 --> 00:02:28,013
The least we can do
is keep up appearances.

42
00:02:28,081 --> 00:02:30,606
Oh, yeah, appearances.

43
00:02:30,683 --> 00:02:33,481
I keep forgetting about appearances.

44
00:02:33,553 --> 00:02:35,885
Rex, you look so tired.

45
00:02:35,955 --> 00:02:41,154
I didn't sleep.
This damn thing is so uncomfortable.

46
00:02:41,227 --> 00:02:44,628
Why don't you move back upstairs
and sleep in our bed?

47
00:02:44,697 --> 00:02:47,860
We're in marriage counseling.
That would confuse things.

48
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:51,131
It's just... I miss you.

49
00:02:51,204 --> 00:02:53,138
I know you do.

50
00:02:54,541 --> 00:02:57,032
If I don't start getting
some sleep soon,

51
00:02:57,110 --> 00:03:00,273
I'll be forced back upstairs
out of sheer exhaustion.

52
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:10,180
Yes, Bre was afraid of many things.

53
00:03:10,256 --> 00:03:13,419
But if there was one thing
she wasn't afraid of...

54
00:03:16,462 --> 00:03:18,396
...it was a challenge.

55
00:04:05,511 --> 00:04:08,810
The day on Wisteria Lane
began like any other

56
00:04:08,881 --> 00:04:12,282
with a cup of coffe
and the morning paper,

57
00:04:12,352 --> 00:04:15,048
and while Lynette read
the business section,

58
00:04:15,121 --> 00:04:17,988
and Gabrielle studied
the fall collections,

59
00:04:18,057 --> 00:04:21,322
and Bre searched for decorating ideas,

60
00:04:21,394 --> 00:04:27,663
Susan scanned the front page
and saw something that caught her eye.

61
00:04:51,224 --> 00:04:54,921
- It's about time.
- Be nice. I come bearing snacks.

62
00:04:54,994 --> 00:04:57,462
Lynette, these cards are sticky.

63
00:04:57,530 --> 00:05:01,159
I know. Preston used the three
of diamonds to scoop jam out of a jar.

64
00:05:01,234 --> 00:05:03,998
We're just thankful we have
49 cards to play with.

65
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:06,470
- Hello, sorry I'm late.
- Hey.

66
00:05:06,539 --> 00:05:09,099
I was just saying
I want to throw a dinner party.

67
00:05:09,175 --> 00:05:10,506
- Really?
- Yes.

68
00:05:10,576 --> 00:05:13,477
I mean, we've never done
a big group thing.

69
00:05:13,546 --> 00:05:15,070
It's a great idea.

70
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:18,242
Paul never likes to have people over,
but to heck with him.

71
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:21,776
- So when is this shindig?
- How about a month from tonight?

72
00:05:21,854 --> 00:05:24,254
- The 16th. Good for everyone?
- Works for me.

73
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:27,782
- Shall we all make something?
- Oh, no. This is my party.

74
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:32,263
I've been wanting to have everyone over
for years. I'm so happy we're doing it.

75
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:34,630
It's gonna be so much fun.

76
00:05:34,701 --> 00:05:36,760
Hey!

77
00:05:36,836 --> 00:05:39,270
I know. Her dinner.

78
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:41,807
How could we have all
forgotten about this?

79
00:05:41,874 --> 00:05:45,742
We didn't forget. Usually when
the hostess dies, the party's off.

80
00:05:45,812 --> 00:05:47,541
- Lynette!
- I'm not being flip.

81
00:05:47,613 --> 00:05:49,342
Just pointing out a reality.

82
00:05:49,415 --> 00:05:53,078
Mary Alice was so excited
about it. It's so sad.

83
00:05:53,152 --> 00:05:57,612
- I think we should go through with it.
- Wouldn't that be in poor taste?

84
00:05:57,724 --> 00:06:01,216
No. It's a way to honor Mary Alice.
It was so important to her.

85
00:06:01,294 --> 00:06:02,989
We could all use a fun night.

86
00:06:03,062 --> 00:06:07,158
Good. I have some new flat bread
I've been dying to show off.

87
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:09,030
- Lynette?
- I'm in.

88
00:06:09,102 --> 00:06:11,570
- I'll make braised lamb shanks.
- I'm still in.

89
00:06:12,305 --> 00:06:14,000
How many will I be cooking for?

90
00:06:14,073 --> 00:06:17,167
Seven. Three couples and Susan.
Does that sound right?

91
00:06:17,243 --> 00:06:21,839
- No, it sounds very, very wrong.
- Is there someone you'd like to invite?

92
00:06:31,824 --> 00:06:34,622
I have an idea.

93
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:41,932
A dinner party? I may be working late.
The Dillman proposal's a complete mess.

94
00:06:42,001 --> 00:06:44,435
You promised to be home
every night this week.

95
00:06:44,504 --> 00:06:47,837
I'll try, but I can't guarantee
anything. This is business.

96
00:06:47,907 --> 00:06:50,569
Says the prince
as he rides off into the sunset.

97
00:06:50,643 --> 00:06:53,009
Boy, did the movies ever get that wrong.

98
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:55,411
You know your problem?
You're very tense.

99
00:06:55,481 --> 00:06:59,008
You should go to a spa or go shopping.
Find a way to relax.

100
00:07:12,965 --> 00:07:15,263
- Hello.
- Where are you?

101
00:07:15,334 --> 00:07:18,030
- Algebra.
- Are you free at four?

102
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:21,232
I'm not sure.
I've got track after school.

103
00:07:21,307 --> 00:07:26,040
Get here as fast as you can.
My husband says I need to relax.

104
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:28,979
You want me to keep
my gym clothes on like last time?

105
00:07:29,048 --> 00:07:31,312
If you would, please.

106
00:07:31,884 --> 00:07:33,977
- A dinner party?
- Yeah. It'll be fun.

107
00:07:34,053 --> 00:07:38,080
- Bree's cooking. Everyone's going.
- I haven't even unpacked yet.

108
00:07:38,157 --> 00:07:41,615
I just, uh, I just need
to chill out for the next few days.

109
00:07:41,694 --> 00:07:44,254
Oh, Tom.

110
00:07:44,330 --> 00:07:46,594
There'll be liquor,
and hors d'oeuvres,

111
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:50,602
and grown-ups without children,
and silverware.

112
00:07:50,670 --> 00:07:54,197
- Remember silverware?
- Honey, can you take this in for me?

113
00:07:54,273 --> 00:07:57,640
- Have you heard anything I said?
- I'm sorry, I'm wiped out.

114
00:07:57,710 --> 00:08:02,306
3 cities in 6 days. My head is pounding.
I'm not ready for a dinner party.

115
00:08:02,381 --> 00:08:05,373
- I already got a sitter.
- Can't you cancel her?

116
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:08,454
Please. Let's just stay in
tomorrow night.

117
00:08:08,521 --> 00:08:11,456
We can get a bottle of wine
and rent a video.

118
00:08:11,524 --> 00:08:15,221
I just want to hang out
with my best gal, that's all.

119
00:08:17,196 --> 00:08:19,562
I was looking so forward
to a night out.

120
00:08:19,632 --> 00:08:23,898
I know, sweetie,
I'm sorry, but I... I'm beat.

121
00:08:23,970 --> 00:08:28,464
I mean, do you remember what
it was like to work a 60-hour week?

122
00:08:32,245 --> 00:08:34,873
A dinner party? Do I have to go?

123
00:08:35,748 --> 00:08:40,879
Given that we're hosting it, I'd say so.
By the way, you won't be drinking.

124
00:08:40,953 --> 00:08:42,420
Why's that?

125
00:08:42,488 --> 00:08:44,718
Because when you drink, you get chatty.

126
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:47,122
No one need know
we're seeing Dr. Goldfine.

127
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:51,095
If you spent as much time working
on our problems as covering them...

128
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:52,289
Not a drop.

129
00:08:52,365 --> 00:08:56,358
This is ridiculous.
And us taking tennis lessons?

130
00:08:56,435 --> 00:09:00,394
Your office may wonder
why you disappear three times a week.

131
00:09:00,473 --> 00:09:03,203
Tennis lessons are a plausible alibi.

132
00:09:05,077 --> 00:09:08,535
So, these tennis lessons.
How are we doing?

133
00:09:08,614 --> 00:09:12,380
My backhand's improving, but
you're having problems with your serve.

134
00:09:13,419 --> 00:09:15,080
Of course.

135
00:09:15,788 --> 00:09:16,812
A dinner party?

136
00:09:16,889 --> 00:09:19,983
It's tomorrow night,
so keep Julie an extra day.

137
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:23,517
Fine. But that's all. Brandi and I
leave Sunday for the cabin.

138
00:09:23,596 --> 00:09:25,029
What cabin?

139
00:09:25,097 --> 00:09:27,861
Brandi wanted someplace
we could get away.

140
00:09:27,934 --> 00:09:31,267
Escrow just closed yesterday.

141
00:09:31,337 --> 00:09:34,170
You can afford a cabin,
but not child support?

142
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:38,609
- The check is in the mail.
- No, it's not.

143
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:41,406
I found my dental guard. I'm ready.

144
00:09:44,216 --> 00:09:45,410
Stop fighting.

145
00:09:45,484 --> 00:09:47,884
We're being as nice
as we possibly can.

146
00:09:47,954 --> 00:09:50,047
Like I said, stop fighting.

147
00:10:00,466 --> 00:10:04,061
Excuse me, Brandi, do you mind?

148
00:10:06,839 --> 00:10:11,401
- Oh, okay.
- Wait. Susan, you're right there.

149
00:10:11,477 --> 00:10:15,208
- You could pick it up.
- I could, but she threw it.

150
00:10:16,015 --> 00:10:20,076
- Don't be petulant. Pick up the can.
- No.

151
00:10:20,152 --> 00:10:23,781
- I can pick it up.
- Honey, stay out of this.

152
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:31,528
Fine. This is so typical.

153
00:10:32,999 --> 00:10:37,993
- I'm sorry. Was that petulant too?
- Pick up the damn can yourself.

154
00:10:38,070 --> 00:10:40,834
Yeah, well, you just go to hell.

155
00:10:45,344 --> 00:10:46,902
You want me to pick it up?

156
00:10:48,147 --> 00:10:49,239
Uh...

157
00:10:57,690 --> 00:11:01,683
Mrs. Warmington said she looked for
Mom's obituary and couldn't find it.

158
00:11:01,761 --> 00:11:06,198
- Did you put one in?
- I've had other things on my mind.

159
00:11:08,601 --> 00:11:11,968
How could you not do that?
People will think we didn't care.

160
00:11:12,038 --> 00:11:16,099
I doubt people will give it much
thought. Don't worry about it.

161
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:18,473
You never talk about her.

162
00:11:18,544 --> 00:11:22,105
She's been dead a month and it's
like you've forgotten she existed.

163
00:11:22,181 --> 00:11:25,275
It's a little early
for this kind of talk.

164
00:11:26,652 --> 00:11:30,884
Maybe when you die,
I won't put in an obituary.

165
00:11:32,425 --> 00:11:36,384
That will be your choice to make.

166
00:11:37,563 --> 00:11:39,997
Assuming you outlive me.

167
00:11:45,838 --> 00:11:49,899
Mom, it's no big deal. We're driving
in for the baptism. Problem solved.

168
00:11:49,975 --> 00:11:53,968
- OK. Fine. You go with Aunt Maria,

169
00:11:54,046 --> 00:11:57,140
and I will take Nana to church.

170
00:11:57,216 --> 00:11:59,343
Take your clothes off.

171
00:11:59,418 --> 00:12:02,251
Uh-huh. OK, I got to go, Mom.

172
00:12:02,321 --> 00:12:04,221
Yes, right now.

173
00:12:04,290 --> 00:12:06,918
OK. You can give me
directions later. Bye.

174
00:12:07,393 --> 00:12:10,760
- Hi, how was school?
- Got an A-minus in my biology exam.

175
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:14,926
You did? Mmm. Well,
let's see what you've learned.

176
00:12:17,703 --> 00:12:20,137
- Who's that?

177
00:12:20,206 --> 00:12:21,901
I don't know.

178
00:12:22,007 --> 00:12:23,998
Hey, you!

179
00:12:28,814 --> 00:12:29,974
Oh.

180
00:12:32,051 --> 00:12:33,746
So, did Mike say anything?

181
00:12:33,819 --> 00:12:36,583
No, but, God, you should've seen
the look on his face.

182
00:12:37,389 --> 00:12:40,881
I'm sure it's not that bad.
He's coming to the party, right?

183
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:44,327
I left three messages.
He's not going to come. Big surprise.

184
00:12:44,396 --> 00:12:48,526
I did everything but foam at the mouth.
I hate when I get that way.

185
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:52,537
Every time I get within ten feet
of Karl, I just become this monster.

186
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:55,403
It's not gonna change
until you resolve your issues.

187
00:12:55,474 --> 00:12:57,601
- You mean, forgive him?
- Mm.

188
00:12:57,676 --> 00:13:01,112
I've lived with this bitterness so long,
I'd be Ionely without it.

189
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:05,014
Honey, get a pet. See ya.

190
00:13:08,053 --> 00:13:10,647
- Son of a...
- It's a business meeting.

191
00:13:10,723 --> 00:13:12,350
It's a frat party.

192
00:13:12,424 --> 00:13:15,291
Regional manager,
corporate manager, head of sales.

193
00:13:15,361 --> 00:13:17,158
Margarita, cigar, sombrero.

194
00:13:17,229 --> 00:13:21,996
Ah, honey, what do you want me to do?
Sit around the hotel watching cable?

195
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:25,559
No, but when I say
we've been invited to a party,

196
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:28,971
don't whine about
your exhausting 60-hour week.

197
00:13:29,041 --> 00:13:33,501
Put on your dancing shoes and take your
children's mother out for a good time.

198
00:13:33,579 --> 00:13:37,140
Fine. You're right.
Let's go to that party.

199
00:13:37,216 --> 00:13:41,050
- I already cancelled the sitter.
- OK. We'll throw the next one.

200
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:45,216
Throw a dinner party?
I don't even have time to wash my face.

201
00:13:48,194 --> 00:13:51,425
No. You know what?
I'm gonna go to this one.

202
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:53,465
You can stay home and baby sit.

203
00:13:53,532 --> 00:13:57,195
Fine. I can handle that.

204
00:14:11,851 --> 00:14:13,182
Thank you.

205
00:14:13,252 --> 00:14:18,554
Gabrielle spent her morning searching
for the mysterious little girl.

206
00:14:18,624 --> 00:14:20,615
Sadly for her...

207
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:25,661
...the mystery was solved
a bit too quickly.

208
00:14:29,468 --> 00:14:32,028
Hey. What's going on?

209
00:14:32,104 --> 00:14:34,470
Have you met Ashley?

210
00:14:36,809 --> 00:14:38,037
Found it.

211
00:14:38,110 --> 00:14:41,705
This is Sheila Bukowski. They moved
into the Miller's old house.

212
00:14:41,780 --> 00:14:44,749
My daughter left her ball
in your yard. I'm so sorry.

213
00:14:44,817 --> 00:14:49,117
Oh. Oh, no, no problem.
Nice to meet you, Ashley.

214
00:14:51,290 --> 00:14:53,224
She's shy. She doesn't say much.

215
00:14:53,292 --> 00:14:56,625
Yeah, but I can see
her little mind working away.

216
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:00,054
Nice meeting you.

217
00:15:02,968 --> 00:15:06,802
Come on, Ashley.

218
00:15:41,674 --> 00:15:46,543
Private sessions?
Why do we need private sessions?

219
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:50,810
Private sessions allow us to work on
the personal issues of both partners.

220
00:15:50,883 --> 00:15:52,350
I don't have any.

221
00:15:52,418 --> 00:15:54,852
My only issue is that
my husband wants to leave.

222
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:57,047
How can I work on that
if he's not there?

223
00:15:57,122 --> 00:16:02,082
There are things I need to discuss with
Dr. Goldfine and I can't have you there.

224
00:16:02,161 --> 00:16:06,530
Why? I'm your wife.
You can say anything in front of me.

225
00:16:06,598 --> 00:16:08,532
All we need is a few more sessions...

226
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:13,003
Damn it, Bree, a few more sessions
isn't gonna fix us.

227
00:16:13,072 --> 00:16:16,303
This is bigger than that.

228
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:18,570
Why don't we do it this way?

229
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:23,604
Rex, you can take the first half-hour.
Bree, you can take the second.

230
00:16:25,417 --> 00:16:27,408
Fine.

231
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:31,320
Oh, and doctor, if what he's about to
discuss has anything to do with

232
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:34,257
adultery, prostitution
or internet pornography,

233
00:16:34,326 --> 00:16:37,386
I would really appreciate you
taking a moral hard line.

234
00:16:52,444 --> 00:16:56,073
Hi, Ashley, remember me?

235
00:16:56,148 --> 00:16:58,139
We... we met earlier.

