00:36:40,865 --> 00:36:44,096
Why is this happening?

469
00:36:47,004 --> 00:36:50,667
Because you can't even
let me pack my own suitcase.

470
00:37:17,001 --> 00:37:19,469
All right. See ya. Have fun.

471
00:37:19,537 --> 00:37:21,971
- Hey. Where are you going?
- Just a sec.

472
00:37:22,039 --> 00:37:25,008
- Mom?
- Don't worry I'm not packing heat.

473
00:37:25,076 --> 00:37:28,705
Hey, Brandi, could you scoot a little?

474
00:37:28,779 --> 00:37:31,839
Just scoot. Thank you. Hi.

475
00:37:31,916 --> 00:37:33,816
- What are you doing?
- I'll be quick.

476
00:37:33,884 --> 00:37:36,614
Brandi, I'm sorry
for the way I treated you.

477
00:37:36,687 --> 00:37:40,179
It was uncalled for and childish,
and it won't happen again.

478
00:37:40,258 --> 00:37:43,386
I have built up
a lot of anger towards you, both of you.

479
00:37:43,461 --> 00:37:46,658
And I realize now
I can't carry that around anymore.

480
00:37:46,731 --> 00:37:51,828
So apology or no apology, I'm moving on.

481
00:37:58,276 --> 00:38:02,178
- Mrs. Mayer.
- Brandi. Brandi, get in the car.

482
00:38:02,246 --> 00:38:06,114
- Mrs. Mayer.
- Please, call me Susan.

483
00:38:07,985 --> 00:38:11,785
I just wanted you to know,
what happened between me and Karl,

484
00:38:11,856 --> 00:38:16,555
things got out of hand because
I thought your marriage was over.

485
00:38:16,627 --> 00:38:20,028
Anyway, I just wanted you to know
I'm sorry, I really am.

486
00:38:22,366 --> 00:38:23,594
Thank you.

487
00:38:27,805 --> 00:38:31,002
And though it came from
an unexpected source,

488
00:38:31,075 --> 00:38:35,512
Susan finally got the apology
she'd always wanted.

489
00:38:40,384 --> 00:38:44,582
Hey, let me take those.

490
00:38:47,958 --> 00:38:51,894
- You're wearing a really big hat.
- Yes, I am.

491
00:38:51,962 --> 00:38:54,089
Listen, the kids are watching a video

492
00:38:54,165 --> 00:38:59,000
which means we've got only about 45
minutes until they actually find Nemo,

493
00:38:59,070 --> 00:39:02,801
so I suggest
that we make the most of it.

494
00:39:02,873 --> 00:39:05,171
By reliving your night out
with the guys?

495
00:39:07,044 --> 00:39:11,378
Lynette... I'm trying.

496
00:39:18,289 --> 00:39:21,656
You look ridiculous in that thing.

497
00:39:21,726 --> 00:39:23,785
Sexy ridiculous?

498
00:39:25,529 --> 00:39:28,657
- Maybe.

499
00:39:28,733 --> 00:39:32,396
I can live with "maybe."

500
00:39:33,971 --> 00:39:36,166
Oh.

501
00:39:41,746 --> 00:39:46,706
You know, it's gonna take
more than just this one night.

502
00:39:46,784 --> 00:39:48,411
- I know.
- Hm.

503
00:39:52,690 --> 00:39:55,420
Ah...

504
00:39:55,493 --> 00:39:58,428
...it looks like we have an audience.

505
00:40:00,798 --> 00:40:04,962
Let 'em look. As long as
they don't try and cut in.

506
00:40:14,879 --> 00:40:19,077
- Dr. Goldfine.
- Bree. We're not scheduled now, are we?

507
00:40:19,150 --> 00:40:22,950
I didn't have time to make an
appointment. Rex moved out today.

508
00:40:23,020 --> 00:40:27,821
I'm very sorry to hear that, but
I'm completely booked right now.

509
00:40:27,892 --> 00:40:32,329
I don't need much time. You have more
insight into my situation than I do...

510
00:40:32,396 --> 00:40:34,489
Bree, we can't talk now.

511
00:40:34,565 --> 00:40:37,864
If you tell me what he told you,
then I could fix the problem.

512
00:40:37,935 --> 00:40:41,996
- I can't do that. It's unethical.
- Why can't you...?

513
00:40:42,072 --> 00:40:45,007
That's my next appointment.
You really need to go.

514
00:40:45,075 --> 00:40:47,168
Dr. Goldfine, please.

515
00:40:48,579 --> 00:40:51,946
Hold on, I'll go and talk to my client.

516
00:41:17,074 --> 00:41:22,603
Bre searched for Rex's
audio tape hoping to find answers.

517
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:25,205
She found answers all right,

518
00:41:25,282 --> 00:41:28,740
but to entirely different questions.

519
00:41:28,819 --> 00:41:32,812
OK. Yeah,
I'll be out in just a moment.

520
00:41:37,962 --> 00:41:40,556
Bree, I'm sorry, he can't wait.

521
00:41:40,631 --> 00:41:44,260
But I can see you first thing
in the morning, eight o'clock.

522
00:41:44,335 --> 00:41:46,826
Eight o'clock.

523
00:41:46,904 --> 00:41:49,338
Sorry to interrupt. Bye.

524
00:41:58,482 --> 00:42:02,919
Yes, I remember the world, every detail.

525
00:42:03,687 --> 00:42:07,487
And what I remember most
is how afraid I was.

526
00:42:07,558 --> 00:42:09,856
- What a waste.

527
00:42:09,927 --> 00:42:13,226
You se, to live in fear
is not to live at all.

528
00:42:15,599 --> 00:42:19,467
I wish I could tell this
to those I left behind.

529
00:42:19,537 --> 00:42:22,370
But would it do any good?

530
00:42:22,439 --> 00:42:24,771
Probably not.

531
00:42:25,743 --> 00:42:31,909
I understand now. There will always
be those who face their fears.

532
00:42:34,184 --> 00:42:38,951
And there will always
be those... who run away.

